{{Lunisolar May}} '''May 18''' is the 18th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Daidō|ja|大同|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[806]] {{ill|June 8|ja|6月8日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Prince Andon ascended the throne and became the 51st Emperor, later known as {{ill|Emperor Heizei|ja|平城天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * (The first year of Datong – June 8, 806 in the Julian calendar – with the enthronement of Emperor Heijō, the era name was changed from {{ill|Enryaku|ja|延暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Daidō|ja|大同|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.) * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1862]] {{ill|June 15|ja|6月15日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Sosho Observatory was moved outside the Hitotsubashi Gate and renamed the Western Book Bureau. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1869]] {{ill|June 27|ja|6月27日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Takeaki Enomoto and others opened the last stronghold, {{ill|Goryokaku|ja|五稜郭|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and surrendered to the new government army. (This marked the end of the Boshin War and the unification of Japan under the Restoration government.) * (Meiji 2, June 27, 1869 in the Gregorian calendar – alternative account of the above event.)
== Births == * {{ill|Hoen|ja|保延|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1139]] {{ill|June 16|ja|6月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Konoe Tennō|ja|近衛天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 76th Emperor of Japan (died [[1155]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 13rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1842]] {{ill|June 26|ja|6月26日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Matsumura Junzō|ja|松村淳蔵|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military personnel (died [[1919]]).
== Deaths == * [[Shōkyō]] 2nd year / {{ill|Genkō|ja|元亨|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1333]] {{ill|June 30|ja|6月30日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hōjō Morotoki|ja|北条守時|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 16th Shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[1295]]). * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1587]] {{ill|June 23|ja|6月23日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ōmura Sumitada|ja|大村純忠|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Christian daimyō who dispatched the Tenshō mission to Europe (born [[1533]]). * {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1705]] {{ill|July 8|ja|7月8日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsunayoshi|ja|徳川綱吉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd lord of the Kishū Domain (born [[1665]]).
