[[cdo:5 nguŏk 18 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[de:May 18 (Lunisolar)]] [[sn:May 18 (Lunisolar)]] [[ko:음력 5월 18일]] [[ja:5月18日 (旧暦)]] [[zh:五月十八]] [[en:draft:May 18 (Lunisolar)]] [[sn:May 18日 (旧暦)]] [[sn:ay 18 (Lunisolar)]] [[ar:May 18 (Lunisolar)]]

{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月十八|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 18일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 18''' is the 18th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|qq=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Daidō|ja|大同|qq=|qq=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} [[806]] {{ill|June 8|ja|6月8日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – Prince Andon ascended the throne and became the 51st Emperor, later known as {{ill|Emperor Heizei|ja|平城天皇|qq=|qq=draft}}. * (The first year of Datong – June 8, 806 in the Julian calendar – with the enthronement of Emperor Heijō, the era name was changed from {{ill|Enryaku|ja|延暦|qq=|qq=draft}} to {{ill|Daidō|ja|大同|qq=|qq=draft}}.) * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|qq=|qq=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1862]] {{ill|June 15|ja|6月15日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – The Sosho Observatory was moved outside the Hitotsubashi Gate and renamed the Western Book Bureau. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|qq=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1869]] {{ill|June 27|ja|6月27日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – Takeaki Enomoto and others opened the last stronghold, {{ill|Goryokaku|ja|五稜郭|qq=|qq=draft}}, and surrendered to the new government army. (This marked the end of the Boshin War and the unification of Japan under the Restoration government.) * (Meiji 2, June 27, 1869 in the Gregorian calendar – alternative account of the above event.)
== Births == * {{ill|Hoen|ja|保延|qq=|qq=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1139]] {{ill|June 16|ja|6月16日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Konoe Tennō|ja|近衛天皇|qq=|qq=draft}}, the 76th Emperor of Japan (died [[1155]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=|qq=draft}} 13rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1842]] {{ill|June 26|ja|6月26日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Matsumura Junzō|ja|松村淳蔵|qq=|qq=draft}}, a military personnel (died [[1919]]).
== Deaths == * [[Shōkyō]] 2nd year / {{ill|Genkō|ja|元亨|qq=|qq=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1333]] {{ill|June 30|ja|6月30日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Hōjō Morotoki|ja|北条守時|qq=|qq=draft}}, the 16th Shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[1295]]). * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=|qq=draft}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1587]] {{ill|June 23|ja|6月23日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Ōmura Sumitada|ja|大村純忠|qq=|qq=draft}}, a Christian daimyō who dispatched the Tenshō mission to Europe (born [[1533]]). * {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永|qq=|qq=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1705]] {{ill|July 8|ja|7月8日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsunayoshi|ja|徳川綱吉|qq=|qq=draft}}, the 3rd lord of the Kishū Domain (born [[1665]]).
