{{Not to be confused with|May 18|qq=May 18}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月十八|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 18일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 18''' is the 18th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Datong (disambiguation)|Daidō]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[806]] [[:en:June 8|June 8]]) – Prince Andon ascended the throne and became the 51st Emperor, later known as [[:en:Emperor Heizei|Emperor Heizei]]. * (The first year of Datong – June 8, 806 in the Julian calendar – with the enthronement of Emperor Heijō, the era name was changed from [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] to [[:en:Datong (disambiguation)|Daidō]].) * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1862]] [[:en:June 15|June 15]]) – The Sosho Observatory was moved outside the Hitotsubashi Gate and renamed the Western Book Bureau. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[:en:June 27|June 27]]) – Takeaki Enomoto and others opened the last stronghold, [[:en:Goryōkaku|Goryokaku]], and surrendered to the new government army. (This marked the end of the Boshin War and the unification of Japan under the Restoration government.) * (Meiji 2, June 27, 1869 in the Gregorian calendar – alternative account of the above event.)
== Births == * [[:en:Hōen|Hoen]] 5th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1139|1139]] [[:en:June 16|June 16]]) – [[:en:Emperor Konoe|Konoe Tennō]], the 76th Emperor of Japan (died [[:en:1155|1155]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 13rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1842]] [[:en:June 26|June 26]]) – {{ill|Matsumura Junzō|ja|松村淳蔵|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsumura Junzō|qq=}}, a military personnel (died [[1919]]).
== Deaths == * [[Shōkyō]] 2nd year / [[:en:Genkō (1321–1324)|Genkō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1333]] [[:en:June 30|June 30]]) – [[:en:Hōjō Moritoki|Hōjō Morotoki]], the 16th Shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[1295]]). * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 15th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1587]] [[:en:June 23|June 23]]) – [[:en:Ōmura Sumitada|Ōmura Sumitada]], a Christian daimyō who dispatched the Tenshō mission to Europe (born [[1533]]). * [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1705]] [[:en:July 8|July 8]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Tsunayoshi|Tokugawa Tsunayoshi]], the 3rd lord of the Kishū Domain (born [[1665]]).
