== Events == * [[:en:Datong (disambiguation)|Daidō]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[806]] [[:en:June 8|June 8]]) – Prince Andon ascended the throne and became the 51st Emperor, later known as [[:en:Emperor Heizei|Emperor Heizei]]. * (The first year of Datong – June 8, 806 in the Julian calendar – with the enthronement of Emperor Heijō, the era name was changed from [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] to [[:en:Datong (disambiguation)|Daidō]].) * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1862|1862]] [[:en:June 15|June 15]]) – The Sosho Observatory was moved outside the Hitotsubashi Gate and renamed the Western Book Bureau. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[:en:June 27|June 27]]) – Takeaki Enomoto and others opened the last stronghold, [[:en:Goryōkaku|Goryokaku]], and surrendered to the new government army. (This marked the end of the Boshin War and the unification of Japan under the Restoration government.) * (Meiji 2, June 27, 1869 in the Gregorian calendar – alternative account of the above event.)
== Births == * [[:en:Hōen|Hoen]] 5th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1139|1139]] [[:en:June 16|June 16]]) – [[:en:Emperor Konoe|Konoe Tennō]], the 76th Emperor of Japan (died [[:en:1155|1155]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 13rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1842|1842]] [[:en:June 26|June 26]]) – {{ill|Matsumura Junzō|ja|松村淳蔵|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsumura Junzō|qq=}}, a military personnel (died [[1919]]).
== Deaths == * [[Shōkyō]] 2nd year / [[:en:Genkō (1321–1324)|Genkō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:June 30|June 30]]) – [[:en:Hōjō Moritoki|Hōjō Morotoki]], the 16th Shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[:en:1295|1295]]). * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 15th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1587|1587]] [[:en:June 23|June 23]]) – [[:en:Ōmura Sumitada|Ōmura Sumitada]], a Christian daimyō who dispatched the Tenshō mission to Europe (born [[:en:1533|1533]]). * [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1705|1705]] [[:en:July 8|July 8]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Tsunayoshi|Tokugawa Tsunayoshi]], the 3rd lord of the Kishū Domain (born [[:en:1665|1665]]).
